	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Unfortunately, it would appear that some bots are learning to adapt - after applying the mod <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB/viewtopic.php?t=373695">http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB/viewtopic.php?t=373695</a><!-- m --> to my own site forums and waiting overnight, two bans were placed. However, 3 more bots managed to successfully create accounts, albeit without websites or signatures (and they were likely unable to fill them in afterwards, as they can't actually activate their accounts).
<br />
<br />Some modifications to that mod might be necessary to make it still show the website field but render it read-only or disabled, so bots still see it and try to fill it in.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


